parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Gear Shifter and Wiring Harness Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear shifter and wiring harness can cause the vehicle to not recognize when it is in park, leading to safety issues such as the vehicle rolling away or draining the battery.
symptoms: The gear shifter fails to shift into park
the vehicle displays a "Shift to Park" message
the vehicle will not shut off
the vehicle will not lock
the ignition continues to beep
and the vehicle may roll away.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk or shudder, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or shudders while driving
the transmission fluid needs to be replaced frequently
and the vehicle may produce a whining noise when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the vehicle to produce smoke and a bad odor, leading to health risks for occupants.
symptoms: Smoke and a bad odor come out of the vents
the torque converter fails
and the vehicle may produce a whining noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to register the vehicle as being in park can cause the vehicle to remain running, leading to battery drain, and potentially causing accidents or rollaways.
symptoms: The dashboard displays a "Shift to Park" message despite the vehicle being in park
the vehicle will not turn off
the horn beeps
and the lights stay on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto stop technology can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off unexpectedly, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off at stop lights or signs
the vehicle jerks or jolts when starting to drive
the auto stop feature delays in engaging or disengaging.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut off unexpectedly, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off in the middle of the road
the dashboard and signals go blank
the vehicle is unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle fails to recognize it is in park, causing the "Shift to Park" message to appear on the dashboard, making it difficult or impossible to turn off the vehicle, which can lead to safety risks.
symptoms: The "Shift to Park" message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle does not turn off
the vehicle beeps incessantly
the vehicle rolls back
the parking brake light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's battery charging system fails, causing the vehicle to shut off in the middle of the road, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: The "Battery Charging System" light comes on
the vehicle shuts off
power steering
lights
locks
and doors fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The exhaust pipe develops holes, causing a safety risk due to potential carbon monoxide leaks into the vehicle.
symptoms: Holes develop in the exhaust pipe
carbon monoxide leaks into the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The catalytic converter fails, causing a safety risk due to potential gas leaks into the vehicle.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the catalytic converter fails
gas leaks into the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The auto stop feature fails, causing the vehicle to delay turning on, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The auto stop feature fails
the vehicle delays turning on.
